.TH MRT_GETSEMSTAT 2 "November 01, 2005"
.UC 5
.SH NAME
mrt_getsemstat \- Gets processing statistics of a RT-Semaphore
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.ft B
#include <unistd.h>

int mrt_getsemstat(\fIint semid, mrt_semstat_t *sem_stat\fP)
.ft R
.fi
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I \Psemid
The RT-Semaphore ID number 
.TP
.I \sem_attrib
A pointer to a \fImrt_semstat_t\fP data structure to store the semaphore statistics
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mrt_getsemstat
Gets processing statistics of a specified RT-semaphore
.PP
This call is restricted to the super-user.
It must be executed by a NRT-process.
.SH "RETURN VALUE
Upon successful completion, a value of 0 (OK) is returned.  Otherwise,
a negative value is returned to indicate an error.
.SH ERRORS
.B mrt_getsemstat
will fail if one or more of the following are true:
.TP 15
[E_MRT_BADSEM]
Invalid Semaphore ID
.TP 15
[E_MRT_FREESEM]
The specified RT-semaphore is free.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR mrt_semalloc(2).
